## MCP Integration: Node.js Debugger

**If nodejs-debugger MCP is enabled, use it for runtime debugging:**

- Set breakpoints in running Node.js processes
- Step in, step out, continue execution
- Fetch current execution location
- Read console output
- Run JavaScript using eval to inspect variables

**Usage:**
```bash
# 1. Start your app with --inspect flag
node --inspect dist/main.js

# 2. Enable in .cursor/mcp.json
# Set "disabled": false for "nodejs-debugger"
```

**NestJS Projects:**
For NestJS, consider also using [@rekog/mcp-nest](https://github.com/rekog-labs/MCP-Nest) to build custom MCP tools that integrate with your NestJS services.

